#: ../../B/broken-arrow.rst:5
msgid "broken arrow"
msgstr "broken arrow"

#: ../../B/broken-arrow.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../B/broken-arrow.rst:9
msgid ""
"[IBM] The error code displayed on line 25 of a 3270 terminal (or a PC "
"emulating a 3270) for various kinds of protocol violations and "
"\"unexpected\" error conditions (including connection to a :ref:`down` "
"computer). On a PC, simulated with ‘->/_’, with the two center characters "
"overstruck."
msgstr ""
"[IBM]様々な種類のプロトコル違反や「予期せぬ」エラー状態(\\ :ref:`down`\\ "
"したコンピューターへの接続を含む)に対して、3270端末(または3270をエミュレートするPC)の25行目に表示されるエラーコード。PCでは、中央の2文字を重ね打ちした‘->/_’で模擬される。"

#: ../../B/broken-arrow.rst:12
msgid ""
"Note: to appreciate this term fully, it helps to know that \"broken arrow\" "
"is also military jargon for an accident involving nuclear weapons...."
msgstr "注:この用語を十分に味わうには、「broken arrow」が核兵器が関わる事故を指す軍事用語でもあることを知っておくとよい……。"
